    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`menu` should be a widget like any other widget, not sugar. The fact that we are internally reusing the same React components should not make it a second-class widget.\n\n`refinementList` should be used only for multiple choices selections (AND or OR). If you want to do a list of radio element, where you can only select one, you should use `menu` instead.\n\nThe current `refinementList` widget code is more complex than it should be because we need to ensure that both `operator` and `singleRefine` are mutually exclusive. This should instead be handled directly inside the `menu` widget (which will not expose the `operator` attribute).\n",
