    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello Algolia Team!\r\n\r\nI've recently spent a considerable amount of time trying to implement a single-selection filter using the useRefinementList hook, under the assumption that it was the go-to solution for all types of facet filtering in React InstantSearch. It was only after delving deep into the documentation and community resources that I discovered useMenu is actually the recommended approach for single-selection scenarios.\r\n\r\nGiven this, I believe it would be highly beneficial for the documentation to explicitly clarify the distinction between useRefinementList for multiple selections and useMenu for single selections. A clear indication of this difference could save developers a significant amount of time and confusion.\r\n\r\nI understand the flexibility and power of Algolia's InstantSearch hooks and appreciate the wide range of customization options available. However, a straightforward guide or note in the official documentation highlighting the specific use cases for useRefinementList vs. useMenu would be incredibly helpful for those of us integrating Algolia into our React projects.\r\n\r\nBest regards",
